# WorkVault
The Premium Sanctuary for Global Elite Talent

## Project Description
WorkVault is a high-end full-stack freelance marketplace designed to connect elite professionals with enterprise clients. It integrates AI-powered career bio generation, real-time project tracking, and secure collaboration into a unified platform.

## Key Features
- AI Career Copilot using Google Gemini API
- Dual Role System (Freelancer and Client dashboards)
- Real-time project tracking with deadline-based indicators
- Secure messaging system between users
- Dynamic portfolio and experience management
- Glassmorphic UI with dark/light mode
- Secure authentication using Supabase

## Tech Stack
Frontend:
- React 19
- Tailwind CSS
- Framer Motion

Backend:
- Node.js
- Express.js

Database:
- Better-SQLite3

Other Tools and Services:
- Supabase (Authentication)
- Google Gemini API (AI Integration)
- Multer (File Upload Handling)

## Architecture
Client Layer: React frontend (SPA)
API Layer: Node.js with Express
Database Layer: SQLite
Authentication: Supabase
AI Integration: Google Gemini API

## Setup Instructions
1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/workvault.git

2. Navigate to the project folder:
   cd workvault

3. Install dependencies:
   npm install

4. Start backend server:
   node server.js

5. Start frontend:
   npm run dev

## Folder Structure
/client       -> React frontend  
/server       -> Backend API  
/database     -> SQLite configuration  
/uploads      -> Uploaded files and images  

## Environment Variables
Create a .env file and add the following:

SUPABASE_URL=your_url  
SUPABASE_KEY=your_key  
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key  

## Testing
- Manual functional testing of all features
- API testing using Postman
- Cross-browser compatibility testing

## Future Scope
- Secure payment integration (Stripe)
- Video conferencing (WebRTC)
- AI-based project scoping assistant
- Analytics dashboard for users

